where formula_223 formula_224 denotes the natural logarithm of the gamma function at formula_130. It is a special function that is easily computed and is standard in some programming languages such as using "log_gamma" in Maxima, "LogGamma" in Mathematica, "gammaln" in MATLAB, or "lgamma" in R and Julia. Roundoff error may cause the returned value to not be an integer.

